text:
Today, I voted to remove House Speaker Kevin McCarthy.  He has proven to be untrustworthy, putting politics over the American people.  I will continue to support Rep. Hakeem Jeffries to be the next Speaker of the House.

nbcnews.com/politics/congres…

Donald Trump faces a $250 million fraud lawsuit because he lied about his wealth, such as the $18 million Mar-A-Lago property is worth $1.5 billion, to cheat banks on loans.  Yet, Republicans think he's a good presidential candidate.  I spoke about it on the House floor.

The Democratic mission was accomplished!  The bill that passed today isn’t the best, but it continues our fight for the American people and funds essential programs, such as Head Start and our border security.  The Democrats delivered today!

cnbc.com/2023/09/30/governme…
Senator Dianne Feinstein was a political trailblazer in every sense of the word.  I spoke about her legacy on the House floor today.

Looking for a new career?  NJ Transit is hiring new bus drivers and providing a $6,000 bonus, if hired.  NJ Transit is picking up new routes, so it's a great time to find your next career.

For more information, visit njtransit.com/careers/bus-op…
The Republican's push for a government shutdown is reckless and irresponsible.  Americans are going to suffer for their lack of leadership.  I spoke about it on the House floor.

Today, I helped open a new Business Opportunity Center to help socially and economically-disadvantaged New Jersey contractors and businesses obtain government infrastructure contracts. It's a cause I fight for daily to create more equality in federal contracting.
To all those observing Yom Kippur, I want to wish you an easy and meaningful fast. G’mar Chatima Tovah. A good final sealing in the Book of Life.

I was proud to attend Johnson & Johnson’s “My Health Can’t Wait” event.  I have been a strong supporter of health screenings throughout my time in Congress and this event screened people for health issues, such as  kidney disease, obesity, and peripheral artery disease or PAD.

In today's Transportation and Infrastructure Committee hearing, I asked Transportation Secretary Pete  Buttigieg about how a potential Republican-led government shutdown would affect funding for the Hudson River Tunnel and Gateway Program.
Republican budget proposals would slash funding for education, law enforcement, and other services Americans need every day.  I spoke about it on the House floor today.
Railroad workers risked their lives to keep food and medicine on our shelves during the COVID-19 pandemic.  They deserve paid sick leave!  I spoke about it on the House floor today.
Today, I met with the Bookers from Orange, NJ. They stopped by to discuss Goldenhar Syndrome, a rare disease that causes incomplete development of bones in the face.

In the last 10 years, state legislators have introduced hundreds of measures to restrict voting access.  Today, @HouseDemocrats and I introduced the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement to protect the right to vote and safeguard our democracy. #RestoretheVote
Extreme MAGA Republicans are pushing a radical and unpopular agenda that hurts American families and workers.  I spoke about it on the House floor.

I really enjoyed my time with Bishop Julius H. McAllister, Sr.; Rev. Anthony Mitchell, Sr.; Elder Coley Woodward, Sr. and the entire congregation of the Union Chapel African Methodist Episcopal Church in Newark at the Family and Friends Day Worship Service.
I want to wish everyone a Happy Rosh Hashanah!  Shanah tovah.

I invite all of you to join me at my State of African American Small Businesses: Activating the Black Community to Build Wealth through Entrepreneurship forum on September 22, 2023 at 3 p.m.  The information is contained in the graphic.  I hope to see you there!
It's National Hispanic Heritage Month.  It's a time to recognize all the significant contributions Hispanic Americans have made, and continue to make, across the country.
Jeremias Castillo won this year’s $25,000 National Honor Society Scholarship winner as a student from Technology High School in Newark.  I congratulated him on the House floor today.

With $8 million from @POTUS the Newark Tree Canopy Initiative can plant hundreds of new trees. 

These trees:
- Keep our city cooler
- Improve air quality
- Provide shade 

We need to do everything we can to protect the environment and give residents more natural space to enjoy.
We have some incredible students in the 10th Congressional District.  Today, I held an event to encourage more of them to apply to West Point.
I am PROUD to be a Democrat because we are putting People over Politics to better the lives of ALL Americans.  I spoke about what we are doing for America on the House floor today.

Instead of funding the government, Republicans want to waste time and taxpayer dollars on a pointless impeachment inquiry.  Even fellow Republicans admit there is no evidence for it.  I spoke about their lack of leadership on the House floor.

I enjoyed my conversations on how to improve the health and safety of local residents with West Orange Mayor Susan McCartney, West Orange School Superintendent Hayden Moore, and West Orange Council President Tammy Williams at the West Orange Health & Wellness Summit.
I was honored to participate in the Essex County commemoration ceremony for the Americans we lost during the terrorist attacks on September 11, 2001.

Today marks 22 years since the horrific, terrorist attacks of September 11- a day that forever changed our nation’s history.   Please take time today to remember the victims of the attacks, the survivors, and their families.

I have been a strong supporter of efforts to promote community safety.  Today, I hosted my Gun Violence Prevention Roundtable with state and local leaders to discuss how we can reduce gun violence in our communities.  In addition, I introduced a bill to get guns off our streets.

Gun violence is a concern for communities nationwide.  Democrats are working to expand background checks and keep dangerous weapons off our streets.  My Safer Neighborhoods Gun Buyback Act would use grants to buy guns from gun owners and protect communities.  @HouseDemocrats

I really enjoyed being a part of the 24 Hours of Peace event in Newark with Mayor Baraka, Redman, Jim Jones, NDO Champ, Councilman Dupre Kelly, and many others to show my support for measures to reduce gun violence and increase community safety.
I want to wish everyone a safe and Happy Labor Day!!

Today, I participated in a summit of local leaders to discuss how to keep our communities safer.  I want to thank Sen. Booker for hosting it.  I support efforts to decrease community violence, like my gun buyback bill to pay gun owners for their weapons. @SenBooker
I had a good meeting today with Orange City Councilmembers Kerry Coley, Tency Eason, and Clifford Ross to discuss the infrastructure funding needs of the township.
Today, I spoke with Dr. Nastassia K. Harris, Founder of Perinatal Health Equity Initiative in East Orange.  We discussed the need for more awareness of Black Maternal Health.

The rising cost of prescription drugs has forced Americans to make the choice between daily needs and life-saving medications. I support Pres. Biden’s work to lower drug prices on 10 life-saving medications for Medicare recipients. @POTUS 

Read more:
whitehouse.gov/briefing-room…

I am always working to help the children of our district get the resources they need to receive a quality education.  I visited the Back-To-School Drive at the Bethlehem Missionary Baptist Church in Newark to support their efforts to help local students.
I was honored to celebrate the 60th Anniversary of the March on Washington and the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. at the "When King Came to Clinton Hill" event in Newark.

Today is the 60th Anniversary of the March on Washington and Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.'s famous "I Have a Dream" speech!  He dreamed of a country free from prejudice.  We must work together to support his dream and make it a reality for ALL Americans! 

naacp.org/find-resources/his…
It was an honor to help veterans and their families find new career opportunities at my Veterans Job Fair today.  It is one way I like to give back to those who have given so much to our country!!

If you are a veteran or family member of a veteran looking for a new career opportunity, please come to my Veterans Job Fair tomorrow (Aug. 24) at 10 a.m.  Register today by contacting my Veterans Affairs staffer Samantha Washington at Samantha.Washington@mail.house.gov.
I always want to make my office available to all my constituents.  Today, I had a mobile office at Essex County's 2nd Annual Citizen Services/ DEDTE Back to School Open House event in East Orange.
I was proud to be with my son, Jack, today at The Green Room ribbon-cutting event.
I want to invite all my district veterans and family of veterans to attend my annual job fair next Thursday.  It is my way of giving back to the Americans who have given so much for our country.

The Inflation Reduction Act provided $369 billion in climate and clean energy investments that is driving job creation, innovation, and slashing climate pollution. I'm excited to continue working with @POTUS to make across the board improvements.
In one year, the Inflation Reduction Act has already brought significant health and economic benefits to families and neighbors in our communities by lowering costs and removing barriers to care.

It was great to speak at the annual conference of the New Jersey State Council of Machinists.

Hard-working Americans are the backbone of our country and unions help secure the wages and benefits they deserve. I will continue to advocate for labor unions and working families.
This great opportunity is fast approaching. We are looking forward to seeing all of you at this year’s Veterans Job Fair. Please reach out to my office with any questions you may have.

I was proud to get $800,000 for the Metropolitan Family Health Network Center in Jersey City.  Now, it can upgrade its facilities and equipment to offer even better health care to the unserved, uninsured, under-insured and homeless population in Hudson County.

I’m devastated to learn of the passing of my good friend, my mentor, my neighbor and my Lieutenant Governor Sheila Oliver.  I want to send my most heartfelt condolences to the entire Oliver family at this tragic time.  I will miss my Bock Avenue neighbor.
It was great to see my friend Rep. Frederica Wilson at her event to promote the health and well-being of Black boys and men. @RepWilson

Today is National New Jersey Day!!  

Today marks the day New Jersey became the third state in the Union. 

Learn more about this special day at nationaltoday.com/national-n…

I've been working diligently with Biden Administration officials to fund the Hudson River Tunnel project and the entire Gateway Program.  Recently, Pres. Biden provided a $7 billion grant for it.  I praised his support of this project on the House floor today.

My bill, the First Responder Access to Innovative Technologies Act (H.R. 3254), just passed the U.S. House of Representatives with a bipartisan vote!!  The bill allows our first responders to use the most innovative equipment to help communities and save lives.

It is time for the Congressional App Challenge!!

If you know a middle or high school student in the 10th Congressional District who is interested in coding, please find more information and register for this year's competition here: 
 
congressionalappchallenge.us…

Joyce Hamlett is retiring as the House Keeper of the Mace.  She is the first African-American woman to hold that position and she has been a tremendous public servant for 35 years.  I was honored to praise her on the House floor.

As a strong environmentalist, I want companies to keep our air and water clean.  I visited Arxada/Troy Chemicals to discuss the specific actions the company is taking to dispose of chemical waste to protect the environment and the health of Newark residents.
House Dems have more than 50 bills to lower gun violence nationwide.  Yet, Republicans do nothing to save lives.  I spoke about it on the House floor.
Trevor Baptiste is an exceptional lacrosse player who grew up in Newark.  I was proud to highlight him and his accomplishments on the House floor.

Right now, I'm managing three bills for Homeland Security on the House floor.

Watch it live here: c-span.org/congress/

GREAT News!!  I've worked diligently to get any possible lead contamination out of school drinking water, including my TEST for LEAD Act.  I'm proud to see the Biden Administration continue to work for the health and security of the American people.

epa.gov/newsreleases/biden-h…

Rev. Jesse Jackson, Sr. is resigning as the leader of the Rainbow PUSH Coalition.  He has been a dedicated civil rights advocate for more than 60 years.  His work and speeches have inspired millions of Americans to fight for justice and equality.  He will be missed.
Every day, Democrats are working to benefit American workers, families and children.    I'm proud to be part of a party dedicated to America and spoke about it on the House floor.
Today, I was proud to receive an award for my dedication to men's health from the Men’s Health Network.
Happy Heavenly Birthday for all you taught me.  Even in death, you are still giving to me!  You are missed.
I want to wish a very Happy Birthday to New Jersey's Lieutenant Governor, Sheila Oliver!!  @LtGovOliver

Too many Americans delay regular health care screenings because they worry about whether their insurance will cover them.  Now, one healthcare insurer wants to make it more difficult to get necessary cancer screenings and care.  I spoke about it on the House floor today.

We must do more to improve the health of people who suffer health complications that could result in a preventable amputation.  I spoke at the APA summit about how my bill, the ARC Act, could save the limbs and lives of 200,000 Americans.
We MUST do more to stop gun violence and save lives in this country!!  I spoke about it on the House floor.

In a committee markup, I heard Republican colleagues talk about the importance of bipartisanship but then vote along party lines.  We are elected to serve the American people, not personal or party agendas.

It is a privilege to represent the great towns and communities of NJ's 10th Congressional District.  Last night, my mobile casework table was at Verona's Summer Concert series when several children stopped by to learn more about the Constitution and the history of our flag.

July is Transit Bus Month for the Federal Transit Administration.  I spoke about my work to put more zero-emission buses on our streets and lower pollution throughout our district on the House floor today.

The Supreme Court rejected affirmative action in education last month.  This decision is going to deny millions of African Americans and other minorities the education they deserve.  I spoke about it on the House floor.
Recently, the U.S. Men's National team won the World Lacrosse Championship.  I congratulated them on the House floor.

I reintroduced the Colorectal Cancer Payment Fairness Act to provide Medicare beneficiaries complete coverage for colorectal cancer treatments they receive during routine cancer screenings by the end of 2023.

As someone who also lost a parent to Colorectal cancer, I appreciate @RepNikema for speaking out and fostering openness around the issue.  I would encourage everyone to get screened soon to ensure we spend as many birthdays as possible with our loved ones.

GREAT NEWS for NEW JERSEY!!

The Biden Administration awarded an almost $7 billion federal grant to build the new Hudson River Tunnel.  I'm proud that my work on the Bipartisan Infrastructure law helped secure this grant.  It's a great day for NJ!!    

yahoo.com/news/us-set-award-…

My prayers and condolences to the families of the two firefighters who lost their lives battling a fire at Port Newark last night.  We must do everything we can to protect the heroes who protect us!

 apnews.com/article/newark-sh…
I want to wish everyone a very Happy Fourth of July!!

I enjoyed being in Verona for the swearing-in ceremony of its town council members.  I want to congratulate Christine McGrath and Alex Roman for their re-election to the council and Christopher Tamburro for his appointment to become the new mayor of Verona.
I want to wish Happy Birthday to Donald, Jack and Yvonne as they turn 25 today.  I am one proud, PROUD papa today and every day!

I am extremely disappointed in the Supreme Court’s decision to block student debt relief.  The current Supreme Court continues to fail to support social justice and deny opportunities to minority communities.

cbsnews.com/news/student-loa…

I'm outraged that the Supreme Court rejected a successful policy that helped millions of Black and other minority students receive the quality education they deserve. This decision is yet another roadblock to success for Black Americans in this country.

nbcnews.com/politics/supreme…

If you are a military veteran, I invite you to attend my annual Veteran’s Job Fair on August 24!

Military members and families have made great sacrifices for our country.  With Essex County and the area's largest employers, we want to give back to those who have given so much.

I want to thank Jeff Brooks, Councilman-at-Large of Rahway, for inviting me to attend the "848: The Criminalization of America" movie screening at Rutgers University.  We MUST stop the racial profiling in America's justice system.

This legislation was the first step toward ending gun violence. It keeps guns out of the hands of criminals and protects victims of domestic abuse.  We must continue the fight by passing a ban on assault weapons and my Safer Neighborhoods Gun Buyback bill.

One year ago today, the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade and denied women the federal right to make their own reproductive health choices.  We must reinstate these rights immediately.  Women should have the right to make their health choices, not state legislatures.

Too many African Americans get amputations to survive Peripheral Artery Disease or PAD, which is treatable if identified early.  I introduced the ARC Act this week to change that and spoke about it on the House floor today.  We must save limbs and save lives from this disease!

John Lewis was a hero, leader, and friend to many Americans. He taught us to stand up for what we believe in and fight the good fight. I was lucky enough to have him as a father figure on the House floor. His legacy continues as an inspiration to those of us still fighting.
June is National Reunification Month.  It is critical that we get families the help and support they need to stay together.  I spoke about it on the House floor.

A lack of awareness of Peripheral Artery Disease (PAD) results in countless preventable amputations each year. My Amputation Reduction and Compassion (ARC) Act requires Medicare and Medicaid to cover PAD screenings for at-risk Americans. We need to #SaveLimbs and lives
It was great to spend time at Newark's South Ward Juneteenth celebration.  I want to thank Councilman Pat Council for sponsoring it.

I enjoyed my time with Assemblyman Reginald W. Atkins, Mayor Dahlia O. Vertreese, Council Member-At-Large Robert Rios, Union County Commissioner Rebecca Williams, and the great people of Hillside at the city's Juneteenth celebration.
It was great to see Council President Tammy Williams, Councilwoman Asmeret Ghebremicael, and all of my friends in West Orange at the township's Juneteenth celebration.

I want to thank Joseph Davis, Executive Director of Brother to Brother, for the invitation to the group's 14th Annual Father's Day Breakfast Celebration and Awards Ceremony.  I heard about its great mentoring programs and celebrated the young men in the program this year.

I have always been a strong supporter of small businesses  throughout my time in Congress.  I spoke with CEO Jill Johnson of the Institute for Entrepreneurial Leadership about how the Congressional funding I've secured from them will provide more growth opportunities.
I always enjoy speaking with Joyce Watterman.  She is a great friend and exceptional Jersey City Council President.  We discussed how we can work together to better the people of Jersey City.
Republicans in Congress want to take money from the American families who need it and give it to the wealthy 1% and billion-dollar corporations that don't.  I spoke about it on the House floor.

A big thanks to our local Congressional Art Competition winner, Newark’s own Jaret Perez, and all the other winners for lending us their beautiful artwork. The halls of Congress are more creative today.

I attended several Juneteenth events in the district to celebrate the end of slavery, like this one in Harriet Tubman Square Park.  It's always great to meet new residents and see old friends at these events!
The end of slavery freed millions of Americans from bondage.  I want to wish everyone a safe and Happy Juneteenth!
I want to wish all the Dads a very Happy Father's Day!!

Too often, men skip routine health screenings and turn minor issues into major ones.  
Today, I introduced the Men’s Health Awareness and Improvement Act to establish an Office of Men’s Health that will create and support programs to focus on men's health nationwide

George Marable is a great man who brought music and culture to our community through his DLV Lounge in Montclair.  Unfortunately, it closed.  But I wanted to praise him and his lounge on the House floor today.

In honor of Men's Health Week, I hosted a Congressional Men’s Health Briefing with my Co-Chair, Rep. Wesley Hunt (@RepWPH).  Too many men struggle to get the physical and mental health assistance they need.  We can change that with more awareness of men’s health issues
June is Caribbean-American Heritage Month.  I spoke about it on the House floor today.

Today, I reintroduced my Payment Choice Act to protect American currency as a form of payment for goods and services.  The bill would make it illegal for stores to reject cash for in-person transactions nationwide.  Every American should have the right to pay in cash.

Today, I enjoyed having Deanna Lescouflair, a Foster Youth Delegate, shadow me all day.  She is from Linden, NJ.  I spent the day teaching her about the legislative process.  @NFYInstitute #fosteryouthvoices
I wanted to post the award I received from the United Jewish Community of Jersey City for my long-standing support of our local Jewish community.
I was proud to receive an award from the UJC of Jersey City for my service and support of our Jewish community during an event to celebrate the groundbreaking of their new synagogue.

I was honored to be one of Monumental Baptist Church's Hidden Heroes this year.  The church celebrates Black men who uplift and inspire their communities.  They wanted to recognize me for my work to help reunite families after incarceration.

One of the best parts of being a Congressman is the chance to help out our local communities and organizations.  I secured $2 million for The Collective, a South Ward Promise Neighborhood Initiative and I wanted to present the check to them personally.
I really enjoyed my time at the Montclair Pride Festival.  I spoke about my efforts to promote equality and combat hate in Congress.
I was proud to celebrate the grand opening of a new BNC Eye Care Group location in Montclair.
I always enjoy visiting local small businesses in my district communities.  This weekend, I had a chance to check out The Grind coffee shop in Jersey City.

Too many men are suffering and dying needlessly because they don’t take their health and wellness seriously. I introduced a resolution today to declare June 12-18, 2023, as National Men’s Health Awareness Week. As men, we need to come together and make our health a priority.
Thank you to BLET President Edward Hall and Vice President and National Legislative Representative Vincent Verna for having me.

Rail workers are essential and kept food and medicine on our shelves during the COVID-19 pandemic.  They deserve paid sick leave.  I discussed my Freight Rail Workforce Health and Safety Act with the Brotherhood of Locomotive Engineers and Trainmen to get them that sick leave.

The Supreme Court said Alabama's Congressional districts violate the Voting Rights Act and discriminate against Black voters.  This decision is GREAT news for voting rights and African Americans across the country.     

nbcnews.com/politics/supreme…

Attention College Students!

If you have been receiving SNAP Benefits, new regulations for students are taking effect June 10th.  You need to reapply for the program through their state agencies by June 9th.

Visit fns.usda.gov/snap/state-dire… find your state’s application

Today, I met with Rutgers-Newark President Nancy Cantor and her team to discuss how to increase funding for educational programs, such as Title III and V, Postsecondary Student Success Grants, and Pell Grants. @Rutgers_Newark

Today is the anniversary of D-Day.  On this day 79 years ago, Allied Forces courageously stormed the beaches of Normandy, helping liberate Western Europe and secure ultimate victory.  Their bravery and determination continue to inspire us to fight for the common good.
I was impressed with President Biden's work to increase the debt ceiling and save millions of American jobs.  I spoke about it on the House floor. @WhiteHouse

At today's hearing, I spoke with Stephen Gardner, Amtrak's CEO (left), and Mitch Warren, Executive Director of the NE Corridor about how we can improve rail travel in our area.  I'm working to secure funding for the Hudson River Tunnel project to make that happen.
I always enjoy my time in Montclair and I was honored to participate in Montclair's African American Heritage Parade and Festival.
My staff stands with me in solidarity to stop gun violence across the nation.
I was proud to vote to raise the debt ceiling and save millions of American jobs.  Here's a picture of me voting for it on the House floor.

Join me tonight at 8 p.m. for the Payne Report on the “All Politics R Local” show.  We’re discussing current political affairs and how they affect the people of New Jersey.

facebook.com/events/97605596…

Gun violence is a local and national epidemic that we must resolve now to save lives.  I hosted a roundtable today with elected officials, local city employees, and community leaders to discuss how we can decrease gun violence in our communities.

I want to thank everyone who attended my Small Business Town Hall.  If you need assistance with a federal grant or other financial aid for your small business, please call my office at  (973) 645-3213.

June is Pride Month. 

It is a time to celebrate diversity and highlight LGBTQ+ issues. But we shouldn't limit this focus to this month alone. We need to make sure diversity and inclusion are an American focus all year.

Gun violence poses a threat to the safety of our families and communities.  I am working to pass my Safer Neighborhoods Gun Buyback Act to fund local gun buyback programs and get them off our streets.  We must do more to protect Americans from this national epidemic. #wearorange

I was proud to honor our service men and women, past and present, at the Mt. Pleasant Cemetery Memorial Day event in Newark.  I love talking with constituents and being in the community to celebrate our country!
Today is Memorial Day.  It is a time to honor the ultimate sacrifice that so many American soldiers and veterans made for our country!

Now is the time to get the job done.  Americans who rely on these essential programs should not be used as pawns in negotiations. We need to increase the debt ceiling for the good of Americans nationwide.

Three years ago today, George Floyd was murdered by local police.  His death showed the horrible police brutality against Black Americans nationwide.  Congress must pass the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act to stop this brutality.  Black Lives Matter!

Speaker McCarthy has been incredibly irresponsible to let debt ceiling negotiations drag on!  We must pass a responsible debt ceiling increase to protect veterans' benefits, save millions of American jobs, and keep the economy working.  I spoke about it on the House floor today.
President Biden's student loan debt forgiveness plan would help Black students pursue their dreams and increase the wealth in Black communities. I spoke about the benefits on the House floor.
Gun violence is an American epidemic.  We must take action to protect the lives of Americans nationwide. #EndGunViolence

Today is the one-year anniversary of the tragic school shooting in Uvalde, TX. Every day, more Americans die needlessly due to gun violence. How many deaths will it take until my Republican colleagues do something to prevent these tragedies?

Black Americans die from fentanyl overdoses at much higher rates than any other community.  But a new Republican bill to classify it as a Schedule 1 drug would make it easier to arrest and imprison Black Americans for minor drug offenses.  I spoke about it on the House floor.
Golfer Renee Powell is an American icon and civil rights pioneer.  I spoke about why she deserves a Presidential Medal of Freedom on the House floor.
I met with the Jewish Community Relations Council today.  These students wanted to discuss U.S. policies regarding Israel and the relationship between the two countries.

I want to thank Councilman Dupre Kelly for organizing the Health Summit and Expo at the Donald M. Payne Sr. School of Technology in Newark.  I spoke to the group and constituents about the need for more attention to the specific health issues faced by Black Americans today.

It was great to speak with Dr. Joyce Harley Wilson, Deborah Collins, and all the members of the Montclair Alumnae Chapter of the Delta Sigma Theta Sorority at the jazz luncheon to support the sorority and Delta Torch Fund.  @MCACDSTNJ
Today, I met with Dianna Houenou, Chair of the New Jersey Cannabis Regulatory Commission.
I enjoyed seeing Mayor Ted Green and hearing about East Orange at the State of the City event last night. @EOCityHall @MayorTedGreen
President Biden has taken several actions that have made our neighborhoods and communities safer.  I spoke about them on the House floor today.
As parents, we tell our children that lying and stealing will not be tolerated in our homes.  It shouldn't be tolerated in Congress either.  I spoke about it on the House floor last night.

As a member of  @TransportDems, my work with the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law has used $220 billion for infrastructure funding to create more than 32,000 specific projects already, including several in NJ's 10th Congressional District.  And this is just the beginning!!
It was a true honor to meet with the members of the US Army War College and hear their stories today.  I thanked them for their service.

First responders protect our health and keep our communities safe.  They deserve to have the most modern and effective equipment possible.  My bill would make sure they have it.
Thanks to @RepDaleStrong for his help as we work to pass this bipartisan safety measure.

In 2012, I lost my father, Rep. Donald M. Payne, Sr., to colorectal cancer.  I hosted a successful Congressional Colorectal Cancer Briefing yesterday to support my efforts to prevent more families from losing their fathers and loved ones to this disease.

Today, I met with Youth Build USA to discuss grant funding. YouthBuild is a job training and education program for at-risk teens and young adults who dropped out of high school. The two programs in Newark build affordable housing and support the community. @YouthBuildUSA

Today, I reintroduced my Colorectal Cancer Payment Fairness to provide Medicare beneficiaries complete coverage for colorectal cancer treatments received during routine cancer screenings by the end of this year.  I spoke about it on the House floor.

This week is Women’s Health Week. Please schedule your routine medical appointments and cancer screenings today.  Routine screenings catch cancer early, make treatments easier, and save lives.  Learn more: preventcancer.org/betteroutc… #CongressionalFamilies

Congratulations to Roselle Park!!  It was awarded more than $25,000 from the NJDEP for a Clean Communities grant to promote more education and boroughwide cleanup efforts.  Keep up the excellent work for the community and environment!  @NewJerseyDEP

Tori Bowie was a three-time Olympic medalist, including a Gold Medal in the 4x100 women's relay at the 2016 Olympics in Rio De Janeiro, Brazil.  Sadly, she took her own life on May 2nd.  I honored her legacy on the House floor.
I want to wish all mothers a very Happy Mother's Day!!

Rail workers have gone too long without paid sick leave.

I'm fighting to change that.   @TransportDems

Thankfully, President Biden stopped the practice from the previous administration of putting immigrant children in cages.  But the MAGA Republicans passed a bill today to put them in cages indefinitely.  It's disgraceful and I spoke about it on the House floor today.

Our railroad workers risked their health and safety to keep the country going during COVID-19.  But the railroad industry denied them paid sick leave to care for their own health.  My bill would give these critical workers the paid sick leave they deserve!

If the U.S. doesn't raise the debt ceiling, the country could default on its debts and cause thousands of job layoffs.  But MAGA Republicans would rather hurt working-class American families than force billionaires to pay their fair share.  I spoke about it on the House floor.

Today, I spoke with David Socolow, Executive Director of the NJ Higher Education Student Assistance Authority, about how we can help students prepare for loan repayments after COVID-19 payment pause is lifted and how to make college affordable for NJ residents. @NJHESAA
I enjoyed my meeting today with Carolyn Welsh, President and CEO of NJ Sharing Network.  We discussed the importance of awareness for organ donation and transplantation systems. @NJSharing

Today, I had a great meeting with Nat Moghe, Rex Reid and Peomelia Tony-Boss.  They are constituents from Roselle who are activists for Family Values @ Work and NJ Citizens Action.  We talked about the importance of paid leave and childcare.  @FmlyValuesWork
Congratulations to Jaret Perez from Arts High School in Newark!  He was awarded Best Overall for this year's Congressional Arts Competition with his work, Golden Boy.  Congrats again, Jaret!  @ahs550

This year marks the 70th anniversary of Seton Hall University's 1953 National Invitational Tournament (NIT) basketball championship, led by Walter Dukes.  As a lifelong Pirates fan, I was thrilled to highlight that team's success on the House floor.

Colorectal cancer is the second leading cause of cancer death for men and women in the United States. 
Please join me and @RepMarkGreen, co-chairs of the Congressional Colorectal Cancer Caucus, for a briefing on the increase in colorectal cancer cases among young adults.

This weekend, I joined @NassansPlace supporters for a 5K to bring more awareness to their exceptional work for families affected by autism.  I secured $750,000 for it in federal funding recently to help it assist more families.

This week, I was proud to present nearly $7 million in federal funding checks to five different cities and organizations in my district for their community projects, such as Roselle and Newark Emergency Services for Families.
This week is National Small Business Week!  Small businesses are the cornerstone of our economy.  Please visit small businesses in your neighborhood this week to support them.

Today, I met with Tiffany Bohlin, CEO of FullBlue360, and Neil Greenstein, owner of ShopRite grocery stores, to discuss an urban blueberry farm project and how it can address food scarcity and environmental problems, such as flooding due to runoff.  I helped get funding for it.

I had a great time Sunday at the 29th Annual Breakfast Celebration of Councilman-At-Large Luis Quintana.  It was a chance to highlight the work of labor leaders, outstanding citizens, and our local students.
